RN  [2]
RM  15368582
RT  Conversion of (2S)-arginine to (2S,3R)-capreomycidine by VioC and VioD
RT  from the viomycin biosynthetic pathway of Streptomyces sp. strain
RT  ATCC11861.
RA  Ju J, Ozanick SG, Shen B, Thomas MG;
RL  Chembiochem. 2004;5:1281-1285.
CC  (2S,3R)-capreomycidine is made as a relatively rare precursor for
CC  non-ribosomal peptide synthesis. The first enzyme (VioC), an
CC  alpha-ketoglutarate-dependent and Fe(II)-dependent L-arginine
CC  beta-hydroxylase, produces (2S,3S)-hydroxyarginine. The second enzyme
CC  (VioD), capreomycidine synthase, converts the product to
CC  (2S,3R)-capreomycidine.
**  VioD looks like an aminotransferase. There are many non-heme
**  Fe(2+)/alpha-ketoglutarate-dependent oxygenase (VioC-like) - see
**  clavaminate synthase system.  228886494 like VioD.
